  "description": "Flew across\u00a0 CR 504 from roost tree in plains cottonwood by Purgatoire River to the north and landed in a short snag with a rock face in the background. After about 1 minute it flew upslope maybe 150 feet to a snag slightly higher in elevation. began to preen. After about another minute it took off to the east and circled mostly below the top of the ridge above the Painted Bunting location and as it gained altitude it disappeared over the ridge to the north not to be seen again that day.",
